<h1 id='authentication'>Authentication</h1>
<blockquote>
<p>To authorize, use this code:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code><span class="c"># With shell, you can just pass the correct header with each request</span>
curl <span class="s2">"https://login.authxpo.com/connect/token"</span>
  -d <span class="s2">"grant_type=client_credentials&amp;client_id=&lt;CLIENT_ID&gt;&amp;client_secret=&lt;CLIENT_SECRET&gt;&amp;scope=connect-orders"</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>JSON Response:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code><span class="p">{</span><span class="w">
  </span><span class="s2">"access_token"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s2">"ACCESS_TOKEN"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w">
  </span><span class="s2">"expires_in"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">3600</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w">
  </span><span class="s2">"token_type"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s2">"Bearer"</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="p">}</span><span class="w">
</span></code></pre>
<p>The XPO API is JSON based. In order to make an authenticated call to the API, you must include your access token with the call.</p>
<h2 id='registering-appliction'>Registering Appliction</h2>
<p>In order to use the XPO API, you must be a current XPO partner. To request access to the API please contact your XPO represenative.</p>

<p>Your XPO representative, will provide you with two keys:</p>

<ul>
<li><code>CLIENT_ID</code></li>
<li><code>CLIENT_SECRET</code></li>
</ul>
